full_content.content: Frigidaire Refrigerator water not coming out
Common reasons your Frigidaire Refrigerator water not coming out
The most common reasons water is not coming out of your Frigidaire refrigerator are a malfunctioning dispenser, faulty water valve or damaged dispenser water tubing.
We can help! Our service technicians have repaired over 15,000 Frigidaire refrigerators. We can fix yours no matter where you bought it.
Most common repairs needed to fix a Frigidaire refrigerator

When water is not coming out of the dispenser in your Frigidaire refrigerator, a defective dispenser may be causing the problem. When you press a glass or container against the dispenser lever to get water, a switch behind the lever should activate a relay that will send electrical current to the water valve so water flows through the dispenser tubing and out of the water dispenser. When the dispenser is malfunctioning, have a service technician visit your home and fix the failure.
How to disassemble the ice and water dispenser on a refrigerator

When activated by the dispenser, the solenoid coil on the water valve lifts the plunger inside the valve to allow water to flow through the water tubing and out of the dispenser. If the valve solenoid coil is bad or the plunger is stuck in the shut position, water won’t flow through the valve. When water is not coming out of the dispenser in your Frigidaire refrigerator when you press the activation lever with a glass or container, have a service technician visit your home and fix the problem.
How to replace a refrigerator water valve video

Dispenser water tubing can get clogged or pinched, preventing water flow to the dispenser when you have Frigidaire refrigerator dispenser with water not coming out. A break in the water line will cause water to leak inside the refrigerator and often onto the floor beneath your fridge. When water is not coming out of the dispenser, schedule refrigerator service to have a technician examine the dispenser water tubing and replace any damaged, pinched or cracked water lines.
How to prevent water dispenser and ice maker problems

How is the Frigidaire refrigerator dispenser water not coming out problem fixed?

Correcting most Frigidaire refrigerator water dispenser problems usually involves replacing the dispenser assembly, water valve or dispenser water tubing. However, there are many potential causes, so a thorough diagnosis is key to fixing the problem. An accurate diagnosis is essential to understanding how much the repair will be.

To avoid replacing unneeded parts we recommend having a Sears Home Services professional perform diagnostic tests to identify the root cause of the problem. Our technicians are experienced at diagnosing all types of refrigerator failures.

Diagnosing modern appliances without proper knowledge and training can be difficult. Without using proper diagnostic techniques, fixing your refrigerator problem will only be achieved through changing parts on a hunch. Appliances, especially in the last 10 years, have become extremely advanced, and many models have electronic parts that are difficult to test. full_content.content: Why won’t water flow from my Frigidaire refrigerator dispenser?
A clogged water filter, frozen water line, or defective inlet valve can impede flow. Check the filter’s expiration and ensure the freezer isn’t so cold it freezes the dispenser line.
How do I know if the dispenser line is frozen?
If there’s a solid blockage in the tubing or the freezer is set too low, water can freeze in the line. Thaw it by raising freezer temperature or manually warming the line with caution.
Could a bad inlet valve block water even if the line isn’t frozen?
Yes. If the valve coil is burned out, water can’t enter the dispenser line. Replacing a faulty valve typically restores proper flow.
When do I need a technician for a Frigidaire fridge with no water output?

If thawing the line and replacing the filter doesn’t work, the valve or control board might be the culprit. A technician can perform advanced electrical tests to identify the exact cause of the failure.

full_content.content: How Does a Refrigerator Ice Maker Work?
Learn how a refrigerator ice maker works and how to keep it in top shape.

A compressor is a mechanical device that increases the pressure of a gas by reducing its volume, essential in various systems including refrigerators, air conditioners, and HVAC units for cooling and refrigeration processes.
A condenser is a component of HVAC and refrigeration systems, responsible for releasing absorbed heat from the refrigerant into the outside air or a water line, thus facilitating the cooling process.
What is a Dual Ice Maker?

A dual ice maker is a feature in some refrigerators that includes two separate ice makers: one in the fridge compartment and another in the freezer section. This setup doubles the appliance's ice-making capacity.

A French-door refrigerator features two doors that open side-by-side on the top section for the refrigerator compartment, with a bottom freezer drawer, combining style, efficiency, and easy access to both refrigerated and frozen goods.
